post_text:
Attn: All Business Owners/Management

Freeland Youth Football has been on a war path, trying to do a complete overhaul on our equipment (Helmets, Shoulder Pads, Training Equipment)

We believe in providing the latest and greatest equipment to ensure that we do our part in player safety.

With over 32,000 dollars invested already (the past four years) we are inching closer and closer to our goals!!

Any donation helps!!

If you own a business or manage a business and want to help put a new helmet on a player or just get your companies name out there...

Look no further!!!

Freeland Youth Football is asking for donations of any size to help our cause.. Upon donation, you will receive an advertisement like the one pictured (hung up at our home games) as well as a 501C3 letter from us with documentation of your donation.

Please reach out if you are interested!!!!

Thanks to our past and future investors!!!

989-205-3801
Sam Morgan, President

989-964-9950
Eric Petre, Vice President
eric.petre@michiganpipe.com

Freeland Youth Football has been on a war path, trying to do a complete overhaul on our equipment (Helmets, Shoulder Pads, Training Equipment)

We believe in providing the latest and greatest equipment to ensure that we do our part in player safety.

With over 25,000 dollars invested already (the past three years) we are inching closer and closer to our goals!! Any donation helps!!

If you own a business or manage a business and want to help put a new helmet on a player or just get your companies name out there... Look no further.

Please reach out if you are interested!!!!

Thanks to our past and future investors!!!

Highly recommended!!

post_text: Last, but certainly not least!! Our 8th Grade Falcons wrapped up a 3rd straight undefeated season and finished their youth careers only losing one game in 5th Grade!! There is a lot of buzz surrounding this team and for good reason. They play extremely well together and have several kids that make plays for them. Coach Pistro, Coach Bakos, Coach Fournier, Coach East, Coach Rump, and Coach Stevens did a great job teaching these kids the importance of playing unselfish football. These kids will be very successful on Friday nights. Thank you for all of your volunteered time Coaches!! A job well done!

Coach Morgan and his staff worked through some things this season and we have 0 doubt that he will have his team ready for ultimate success next year. The goal is to mold young men into positive students and players and this staff does just that!! Putting the kids and team first will always be what Sam does. Everyone that is coaching in the league next year stems from his coaching tree. Let go finish strong Prez!!!

post_text: The 5th Grade Freeland Falcons finished their season strong by handing Ithaca a 52-6 loss!! The 2025 Falcons finished their season scoring 214 points while only letting up 20 points. And I stress the word family!!
